            "source": [
                "# Day 59: Concept Activation Vectors (CAV)\n",
                "\n",
                "Beyond individual words, we want to know if abstract concepts like **\"Aggression\"** or **\"Politeness\"** are activated inside the model.\n",
                "We use a mock embedding space to demonstrate how CAVs work."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import sys\n",
                "import os\n",
                "\n",
                "# Add root directory to sys.path\n",
                "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('../../'))\n",
                "\n",
                "from src.interpretability.cav import CAProbe"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 1. Init Probe\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "probe = CAProbe()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 2. Test Politeness\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "text = \"Could you kindly help me?\"\n",
                "activations = probe.analyze(text)\n",
                "print(f\"Input: '{text}'\")\n",
                "print(f"Concept Activations: {activations
                }")\n",
                "# Expect Politeness > Aggression"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## 3. Test Aggression\n"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "text_2 = \"I hate this stupid tool.\"\n",
                "activations_2 = probe.analyze(text_2)\n",
                "print(f\"Input: '{text_2}'\")\n",
                "print(f"Concept Activations: {activations_2
                }")\n",
                "# Expect Aggression > Politeness"
            ]
        }
    ],
